<TITLE>Tyna1025.html</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
October 25, 1996<BR>
<BR>
Today I continued the lesson Stacey and Eric had spontaneously started yesterday that went fantastically!  We were planning on focusing this week on the water cycle and pollution but everything has been pushed back to encompass this activity that the kids went after so wholeheartedly.  The kids each chose an animal they wanted to be.  They performed some research on the Internet, but Stacey, Eric and I thought it would be a good idea to give them more time in the school library - so that's what I did!<BR>
They worked very well together and independently in the library and I was very proud of them.  I was also very pleased to find that I harbored no remaining disappointment about my failed lesson on Wednesday.  It was as if walking into that room on the brand new morning gave us all a brand new slate to work upon.  It was definitely a feeling that I liked.<P>

