<TITLE>Tyna115.html</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
November 5, 1996<BR>
<BR>
The kids have Friday off this week so I came in today to make up for it.  I took them to the computer lab and had them type in their stories about the animal they chose.  It went really well!  I had a really good time and they seemed to enjoy the change. I noticed that many of them have a difficult time typing - I am not sure if this is due to the lack of a typing class in their background or if they simply don't get typing.  I had one of the students challenge me that I could not type as fast as I wanted him to type.  I love nothing more than a challenge!  I didn't bother to warn him that I had been a licensed computer processor for 5 years.  I typed the next sentence in his story in a matter of seconds and just as quickly erased it so he would have to do it himself.  I sort of enjoyed watching his face take on a look of pure astonishment! 
 He became a bit frustrated in the end and I ended up helping him type in the remainder of his story to keep him on track with the others, but I didn't mind.  <BR>
The kids have been very lighthearted with me, teasing me quite a bit, always quick to apologize if they believe for a minute they have actually hurt my feelings.  Another teacher assured me that the students only really pick on the teachers they truly like.  I suppose I can take their ribbing as a compliment - just as long as that is what 
it means!<P>


</BODY>
</HTML>
