<BODY>
Journal 10/27<BR>
Stacey Maguire<P>


I finished 2 classroom activities on Thursday: Why We Test Water and the Incredible Journey - Biology Group.  They are up on the Web as soon as Dr. Doody drops the folder in.  I also typed up several of my journal entries.  I wrote a note to Dr. Doody regarding my journals.  I wanted to know if I should edit my journals more.  I am including students names which concerns me.  I am only saying positive things generally, but 
I wasn't sure if I should include the names.  He said the entries looked good.<P>


The students were good Thursday.  Brandon and Gina were absent.  The lesson went well and we extended it until the end of next week.  Tyna is going to continue researching with them on Friday and start the acid rain lesson on Monday.  When Eric and I go to Gouverneur on Wednesday, they should be ready to start writing their stories.<P>


They loved going to the SWAMP.  Mike and Mrs. French joined us.  They seemed pleased with our lesson and the student involvement. They also seemed to like the MAC lab.<P>


The students have such different responses when asked to take notes.  Most don't want to for whatever reason, except Charity.  By the time we left the MAC lab, she must have had 1-11/2 pages of notes.<P>


They all tried to find out information about the species they picked by performing Net Searches.  Some had more luck than others.  I wished we had more than 30 min. Eric and I need to work on the rubric for the short story.  I'd like to give it out before they start writing.<P>

