Journal 10/30<BR>
Stacey Maguire<P>


Eric and I discussed our lesson on the trip over.  We had to make some changes as a result of what was accomplished on Monday.<P>


Boy was it wild at the middle school today.  Mike had so much going on that he didn't have any time to talk with us.  Something was up.<P>


Our students were "up".  Erica's sister is in the hospital waiting to have her baby.  Everyone was excited.<P>


Jen and Erica have good first drafts done and worked on typing up their stories. Charity had an awesome draft mostly done.  She has excellent habitat detail.  Kate kept her original species, the northern pike.  She has a good picture but needs to research more detail about the habitat.  Brandon is in the midst of his weasel story.  Steven is Flip the fox and he's also in the midst of his draft.  Andy is pretty much in the same situation.  Gina has picked the beaver but she is not here today.<P>


They know they need to cometo SUNY tomorrow with their drafts done.  We will start working on their posters for our bulletin board project.  There seem to be many questions about acid rain so I'm going to put together a worksheet for tomorrow.<P>


Eventually we're going to have the stories typed for the bulletin board and the Web. <P>



We gave them the rubric for how they are being graded.  Hope that will help them. 
  <P>

