<BODY>
Journal 10/31/96<BR>
Stacey Maguire<P>


The students worked on their short stories and posters today.  Brandon and Andy drew great scenes.  Jennifer and Erica are working together and combining their species: cottontail and raccoon on one poster.  Steven is the red fox.  Charity and Kate are working together on one poster also.  They are doing the snapping turtle and northern pike.  Brandon is doing the weasel and Andy is doing the white-tailed deer.  Gina is still doing the beaver.<P>

We collected their rough drafts today and split them to read and make comments.  We're faxing them to Gouverneur tomorrow so the students can work on them.  We should ask Mike to fax them back (corrections made) by Tuesday.  We could have typed copies and final grades when we see them on Wednesday.<P>


We had the Halloween party thanks mainly to Donna and it was great.  A friend of mine dressed up in a ghost-like costume and the students went crazy.  They swarmed around her and kept trying to find out who she was.  They thought she was Tyna.  At least some did.  Kate even thought it might be Dr. Doody.    I finally told my group that they had seen her in the MAC lab when we had been there.  Andy's eyes got big.  He knew that she was the woman who had sat in back of him.  He appeared amazed.<P>

