<TITLE>Stacey118.html</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
Journal 11/8<BR>
Stacey Maguire<P>


The students were good yesterday.  They shared their stories.  We probably should have put the grades on them after  they had read them.  However, they ahd comments on their drafts and if they chose not to take our suggestions, they didn't get as high a grade as they could have.  When writing an acid rain story, one must talk about acid rain.  Overall, the stories were very good.  I was pleased.<P>


Tyna said that she tried to get them to make the changes Tuesday.  What else can you do?<P>


The students are working on the acid rain crossword puzzle.  Some weren't too happy that it wasn't easy.  Oh well.  They should know it wouldn't be easy.   How could it be challenging if it were easy.  I want them to THINK!  They are capable of so much but some don't believe they are.  Sometimes I just want to yell at them that they are smart, so smart.  There is not a one who can't get A's in this course.  But, motivation seems to be a problem often.  We've tried many things.  I just think it must be hard to have so many teachers.  So many personalities to try to figure out.<P>


We will be taking them on a field trip to the Quant. lab at SUNY in December to perform heavy metal testing on our water samples.  We should be able to do mass spec and atomic absorption.  Dr. Hepel was so interested.  Can't wait.<P>

