<BODY>
Journal 11/13<BR>
Stacey Maguire<P>


Mike had to cancel the field trip to Cranberry Lake this morning.   He tried to reach all of us but couldn't get Eric and Rita.  They drove to Cranberry Lake.  Oh no. Apparently only 3 of 16 students came prepared for the cold.  He had no choice. I'm pretty sure that after this afternoon with him, they had wished they were prepared.<P>


We will have to find out when this trip will be rescheduled, if at all.  We are running out of weeks.<P>


Eric and I talked to Mike after our afternoon seminar and explained to him that because the students weren't prepared for today, we are not prepared to put together another lesson for tomorrow.  Our lessons when we visit the river span 2 days (Wed and Thurs).  We decided that since Wed. was cancelled so would Thursday.  Eric and I didn't want to make the call for the Biology group though.  We tried to reach Donna but could only leave a message on her machine.  He could still bring the biology team but that would probably not be feasible.  Eric is going to call Melissa and Rita.  I'll get in touch with Donna and Tyna.<P>



</BODY>
</HTML>
