<DT><!-- List Tag --><DL>
<DT><DT><HTML>
<DT><DT><HEAD>
<DT><DT><TITLE>lesfiv</TITLE>
<DT><DT></HEAD>
<DT><DT><!-- Body Tag --><BODY BACKGROUND="back2.gif">
<DT><DT></BODY>
<DD>     <DD>     <CENTER><B><!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=5><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#AFCEFF">Lesson Plan #4 - Plants</FONT></FONT></B></CENTER><BR><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <CENTER><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#290A64"><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="lespfve">Task Analysis</A></A></FONT></CENTER><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <CENTER><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#290A64"><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="assmnt">Summative Assessment</A></FONT></CENTER><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <CENTER><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="assmnt#port5">Portfolio Assessment</A></CENTER>
<DD>     <DD>     <!-- Horizontal Line Tag --><HR WIDTH=100% SIZE=3 NOSHADE>
<DD>     <DD>     
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <B><!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#AFCEFF">Lesson Target:</FONT></FONT> </B>  <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Plant Classification <BR>
<DD>     <DD>       and importance      <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <B><!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#AFCEFF">Science Concept:</FONT></FONT></B><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Plant classification taught through the differences in leaves.    Importance of plants 
<DD>     <DD>     to all ecosystems.<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <B><!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#AFCEFF">Science Skills:</FONT></FONT></B><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Listening, observation and collection of data<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Interpretation of data observed<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <B><!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#AFCEFF">Interdisciplinary Connection:</FONT></FONT></B><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Reading skills used in using a key to interpret leaf classification.    Art skills 
<DD>     <DD>     used to relate importance of plants.<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Duration: 1 week<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <B><!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#AFCEFF">Lesson outcomes:</FONT></FONT></B><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     
<DD>     <DD>     <H3> </H3>
<DD>     <DD>     <B><!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4>Students will:</FONT></B><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <OL>
<DD>     <DD>     <LI>Collect leaves to be analyzed using rudimentary skills to     <!-- List Tag --><DL>
<DD>     distinguish different leaves to get a good sample.
</DL>
<DD>     <DD>     <LI>Use a key efficiently to classify trees using leaves collected.<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <LI>Gain and appreciation for plants.<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <LI>Draw a cartoon to relate the importance of plants to all     <!-- List Tag --><DL>
<DD>     ecosystems.
</DL><DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     </OL>
<DD>     <DD>     <B><!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#AFCEFF">Overview:</FONT></FONT></B><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     In this lesson the students will gain an understanding of how to use reference material to identify and classify plants from leaf samples.   They will then use basic knowledge to explore the importance of plants to the world ecosystem and show this knowledge creatively in a cartoon form.<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     
<DD>     <DD>     </BODY>
<DD>     <DD>     </HTML>
<DD>     </DL>
</DL>
