<H3><CENTER>Summative Assessment</CENTER> </H3>
<STRONG><BR>
</STRONG>
	<cite>**the following is an assesment provedure that will be used for each student at the conclusion of each lesson; this evaluation method is a supplemental assessment that will work hand-in-hand with the journals, quadrants, and various constructed material done by class members and groups.  Each individual skill listed for the unique lessons will be evaluated and graded using an M, D, or N.</cite><BR>

<H3><EM>Students Name:</EM>
 ______________________________________ </H3>
<STRONG><BR>
</STRONG>

<H5>M =
Mastery.  <CITE>The student has demonstrated full understanding of the concept or skill.<BR>
</CITE>

<H5>D = Developing.  <CITE>The student has demonstrated progress in understanding the concept or skill.</CITE>
<BR>

<H5>N = Not Yet. <CITE> The student has not significantly demonstrated understanding of the  concept or skill. 
</CITE>
<STRONG><BR>
</STRONG>
<STRONG><BR>
</STRONG>

<H3></H3>

							
<H3>       </H3>
<STRONG>Concept or Skill:<BR>
</STRONG>
<STRONG><BR>
</STRONG>
<STRONG><CITE><EM><!-- Anchor Point Tag --><A NAME="assessment1">River Utilization</A><BR>
</EM></CITE></STRONG>
<STRONG><BR>
</STRONG>
A. Linguistic Assessment (brainstorm activities)<BR>
B. Reflective Assessment (personal journal entry) <BR>
