<H2>Daily Journal Writing Assessment </H2>

<H2>5 Point Rubric Scale </H2>
<STRONG><BR>
</STRONG>
<STRONG><BR>
</STRONG>
5-  The concept or skill or activity required has been clearly written and identified 
with few significant errors and excellent grammatical structure.  The student has 
included the date and pertinent information, as to what activities he/she participated 
in a given day.  The student has included a reflective statement on what he/she has 
discovered and learned.  The student has included suggestion of possible solutions 
to problems encountered.  The student has included drawings of the sites activities 
for that day.<BR>
<BR>
4-  The concept or skill or activity required has been addressed in complete sentences 
with good grammatical structure. The student has included the date and pertinent 
information, as to what activities he/she participated in a given day. The student 
has included a reflective statement on the days assignment.  The student has included drawings 
of the sites activities for that day.<BR>
<BR>
3-  The concept or skill or activity required has been adequately addressed with some 
grammatical errors within sentences.  The student has included the date and activities 
that he/she participated in a given day.  The student has included a satisfactory 
statement on the days assignment.<BR>
<BR>
2-  The concept or skill or activity has not  been adequately addressed in complete 
sentences. The student has numerous inconsistencies in both clarity and form.  The 
student did not  provide pertinent information on the days activities.  The student 
has not clearly included the assignment for that day.<BR>
<BR>
1-  The concept or skill or activity has not been provided. The student has provided 
incomprehensible written work.  There is no evidence of organization.  Written work 
is incomplete.     <STRONG><BR>
</STRONG>
<STRONG><BR>
</STRONG>
<STRONG><BR>
</STRONG>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
