<html>
<head>
<title> Chapter 6B 9-16</title>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#0000ff" vlink="#ff00ff">

<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=462 HEIGHT=87  SRC="../FACBOOK.GIF"></CENTER>
<BR>
<BR>
<A NAME="VI.  RETIREMENT, DISABILITY AND DEATH BENEFITS"><CENTER><B>VI.  RETIREMENT, DISABILITY AND DEATH BENEFITS</B></CENTER></A>
<br><br>
<dt>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B9"><i><BLOCKQUOTE>9</A>.	TO OBTAIN AN ESTIMATE</i>
<dt><br>
		<dt>A member of any Tier program who wishes to obtain an estimate of the  maximum allowance and all options, must furnish the Retirement System with her or his name and membership number, contemplated date of retirement, salaries for the five years preceding the date of retirement, and the sex and date of birth of the beneficiary who might be named at retirement.</BLOCKQUOTE>

	</dl>
<dt>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B10"><i><BLOCKQUOTE>10</A>.	RETENTION OF MEMBERSHIP (NON-VESTED MEMBERS)</i>
<dt><br>
		<dt>Generally the membership of any person credited with less than 10 years of NYS service will terminate when seven years have elapsed since (s)he last rendered at least 20 days of credited service in a school year.</BLOCKQUOTE>

	</dl>
<dt>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B11"><i><BLOCKQUOTE>11</A>.	CREDIT FOR MILITARY SERVICE</i>
<dt><br>
		<dt>Military service may be credited in the NYS Teachers' Retirement System under certain conditions.  For specific information, a member should write to the System directly or confer at a consultation site with one of the System's information representatives.</BLOCKQUOTE>

	</dl>
<dt>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B12"><i><BLOCKQUOTE>12</A>.	LOANS</i>

<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B12a">a</A>)	Tier I and II

<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B12ai">i</A>)	Eligibility
<dt><br>
				<dt>Any pre-July 27, 1976 member (i.e., Tier I and Tier II member) in active service or on leave of absence, under age 70, who has at least one year of service credit and who has at least $400 in accumulated member contributions (and interest) in the System may borrow from them once during each six-month period.

			</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B12aii">ii</A>)	Amount
<dt><br>
				<dt>The minimum loan is $300.  The loan amount cannot exceed the less of 75% of the member's accumulated contributions in the System or the total of principal and interest which can be repaid by age 70 by payments of 10% per year of the member's contract salary at the time the loan is issued.

			</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B12aiii">iii</A>)	Repayment
<dt><br>
				<dt>A loan must be repaid in equal monthly installments directly to the Retirement System, or through regular payroll deductions.  Direct repayment is required only during the 10 school months, September through June, although additional payments in multiples of the monthly installments may be made at any time.  Payment must be made at an annual rate of at least 2% of the member's contract salary and sufficient to repay the loan by age 70.                                

			</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B12aiv">iv</A>)	Loan Forms
<dt><br>
				<dt>There are two loan application forms:

<dt><br>
<dt><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B12aviiia">(a)</A>	5-Year Loan Application--This form has been distributed to employers and should be used exclusively for loans with repayment terms of five years or less.  The required monthly repayment on a "5-Year" loan may be substantial.  Inasmuch as the repayment amount cannot be reduced after the loan check is cashed, members should consider contacting the System prior to submitting the loan application to receive an estimate of the monthly repayment amount.

				</dl>
<dt><br>
<dt><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B12aviiib">(b)</A>	5-Plus Loan Application--This form may only be obtained from the System's loan department.  Members requesting a 5-Plus Loan Application are automatically  provided with the approximate taxable amount of the loan to help them determine their potential federal tax liability should they choose to extend their loan payments beyond five years.
<dt><br>
<dt>If the loan application filed is complete and correct, eligible members are generally granted loans less than one week after the System receives the application.
</dl>
</dl>
</dl>
<dt><br>
<dt><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B12b">b)</A>	Tier III and IV

<dt><br>
<dt><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B12bi">i</A>)	Eligibility
<dt><br>
				<dt>Be in active service (i.e. employed by a participating employer of the Teachers' Retirement System or on a paid leave of absence).  Submit a copy of your leave authorization with this application.
<dt><br>
<dt>Have at least one year of member service
<dt><br>
<dt>Not have taken a loan within 12 months
<dt><br>
<dt>Not have an outstanding loan more than two months delinquent or in default

			</dl>
<dt><br>
<dt><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B12bii">ii</A>)	Finance Charges
<dt><br>
				<dt>A $30.00 service charge is added to the amount to be repaid.
<dt><br>
<dt>Interest is charged at the annual rate of 7%. (Interest rate is always 1% less than the System's valuation rate).
<dt><br>
<dt>Life insurance is charged at the annual rate of .10%.  Your loan is fully insured beginning 31 days from the date of issuance.  Once your loan is in default, insurance coverage ceases.
<dt><br>
<dt>A charge of $2.00 is added to your loan balance for each bad (returned) check.
<dt><br>
<dt>A charge of $2.00 is added to your loan balance for each delinquent payment.

			</dl>
<dt><br>
<dt><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B12biii">iii</A>)	Loan Terms
<dt><br>
				<dt>Minimum loan is $1,000.
<dt><br>
				<dt>Loan may not exceed 75% of your Contribution Fund.
<dt><br>
				<dt>A new loan will be combined with any existing loan.
<dt><br>				
				<dt>Loan must be repaid within 5 years.
<dt><br>
				<dt>Minimum annual payment is the greater of 2% of current contract salary or the amount which makes the loan repayable within 5 years.
<dt><br>
<dt>Repayment can be payroll deducted or by direct (coupon) method.
</BLOCKQUOTE>


	</dl>
<dt>

<dt><A NAME="6B13"><i>13</A>.	TRANSFERS</i>
<dt><br>
		<dt>Persons who hold valid memberships in two public retirement systems in New York State at the same time may receive credit in one system for the service rendered and credited in the other system through direct transfer.  For example, a member of the NYS Employees' Retirement System who changes jobs and joins this System may transfer credit from the Employees' Retirement System to the Teachers' Retirement System providing memberships in both systems are valid at the time of transfer.
<dt><br>
<dt>It is important to note that if a member is eligible to transfer and fails to do so and membership is terminated in the former system, then (s)he can never receive credit for that service.
<dt><br>
<dt>Once a transfer has been completed, the earlier of the membership dates in the two systems will be retained.  Purchase of prior service, explained above, does not change a person's membership date.

<dt><br>
	</dl>
<dt>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B14"><I>14</A>. INFORMATION ABOUT RETIREMENT</I>
<dt><br>
<dt>Annually each member receives a statement from the System containing updated information about his/her membership.
<dt><br>
<dt>Periodic newsletters and other publications are sent to members and school administrators.
<dt><br>
<dt>The System maintains a personal consultation service for members at selected locations throughout the State as well as at System headquarters in Albany.  Each fall consultation schedules are sent to the College and are available from the Office of Human Resources.
	</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B15"><i>15</A>.	SOCIAL SECURITY AND YOUR RETIREMENT PLAN</i>
<dt><br>
		<dt>Since 1957, teachers who are members of the New York State Teachers' Retirement System have been eligible for Social Security coverage.  Members in service in 1957, whose memberships have continued since then, are covered only if they elected coverage when it was offered.
<dt><br>
		<dt>Social Security coverage is mandatory for all other teachers upon joining the Retirement System.  A substitute or part-time teacher who desires Social Security coverage for teaching employment must first join the Retirement System.  Substitute or part-time teachers who do not join the System still must contribute to Medicare.


	</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B16"><i>16.	FILING FOR RETIREMENT</i>
<dt><br>
		<dt>To initiate retirement, a member must file the proper form.  A retirement application must be on file with the Retirement System at least 30 but no more than 90 days before the date that retirement is to become effective.  The retirement application may be obtained from the System or the Office of Human Resources.  Decision regarding the form of allowance must be received by the last business day of the month in which the retirement is effective.
<dt><br>
		<dt>Many members have already filed acceptable proof of date of birth with the System.  For those who have not, an original or certified copy of any one of the following documents will serve as satisfactory proof: a birth certificate, a hospital record established during the first five years of  life certified by the custodian of the record, or a church baptismal record established during the first five years of life which shows the date of birth.
<dt><br>
		<dt>If one of the documents listed above is not available, then at least two of the following must be furnished: a school record from grade six or earlier, a church record, a state or federal census record, a bible or other family record, an insurance policy written at age 35 or before (applications for insurance are unacceptable), a marriage record, a passport, a military record, an immigration or naturalization record, a report of confidential social security benefit information (form SSA-2458) from the Social Security Administration.  Any of the foregoing documents must, of course, show the member's age or date of birth.
</dl>
</dl><BR>
<BR>

