<TITLE>Master of Science in Teaching -- SUNY Potsdam</TITLE>
<BODY background="blue_paper.gif">
<H1><B><A NAME="MST">Master of Science in Teaching</A></B></H1>
<B><A NAME="MST Elementary Education"><H2>Elementary Education</H2></A></B>
	The Master of Science in Teaching (elementary education) prepares persons possessing a baccalaureate degree to teach and to become provisionally certified in grades N6.<BR>
<FONT SIZE=3><B>Core Requirement:	3 credit hours</B><BR>

<A HREF = "gradcourses.html#GRED600">GRED 600</A>	Advanced Philosophical Foundations of Education<P>
	
<B>Methods & Practicum:	33 credit hours</B><BR>
<A HREF = "gredcourses500.html#GRED527">GRED 527</A>	Reading and Language Arts Instruction and Practice<BR>
<A HREF = "gredcourses500.html#GRED528">GRED 528</A>	Advanced Reading and Language Arts Instruction and Practice  
			(Prereq:  GRED 527)<BR>
<A HREF = "gredcourses500.html#GRED565">GRED 565</A>	Elementary Math:  Content & Methods<BR>
<A HREF = "gredcourses500.htmll#GRED566">GRED 566</A>	Elementary Science:  Content & Methods<BR>
<A HREF = "gredcourses500.html#GRED567">GRED 567</A>	Elementary Social Studies:  Content & Methods<P>

<A HREF = "gredcourses600.html#GRED614">GRED 614</A>	Technology in Education<BR>
		<B>or</B><BR>	
<A HREF = "gredcourses500.html#GRED518">GRED 518</A>	Microcomputer Applications in Education<P>

<A HREF = "gredcourses650.html#GRED696">GRED 696</A>	Supervised Clinical Experience/Student Teaching (6 credit hours)<BR>
<A HREF = "gredcourses600.html#GRED613">GRED 613</A>	Teaching Internship  (6 credit hours)<BR>
<A HREF = "gredcourses650.html#GRED678">GRED 678</A>	Student Teaching Seminar: Issues and Ideas in American Education<BR>  
			(3 credit hours)<P>
<B>Electives:	6 credit hours</B><BR>
	Two 3-cr. hour electives (under advisement)*<BR>
	(must have at least 3 cr. in CIS computer proficiency or take <A HREF = "gredcourses500.htmll#GRED518">GRED 518</A> as one elective)<P>

*<A HREF = "gredcourses650.html#GRED677">GRED 677</A>, Development and Learning for Teachers, is strongly recommended if undergaduate work does not include a course in developmental, adolescent or educational psychology.<P>
	
<B>Culminating Experience:</B><BR>
	- Passing score on the ATS-W portions of the New York State Teacher Certification Exam<BR>
	- Successful completion of a Culminating Experience in the School of Education.<BR>
<UL>	NOTE:  Successful completion of the CST portion of the NYSTCE is required for permanent certification.</UL><P>

<H1><B><A NAME="MST SEC ED">Master</A> of Science in Teaching</B></H2>
<H2><B>Secondary Education</B></H2>
	The Master of Science in Teaching (secondary education) prepares persons possessing a baccalaureate degree to teach academic subjects and to become provisionally certified in grades 712.<P>

<B>Core Requirements:	6 credit hours</B><BR>
	<A HREF = "gredcourses600.html#GRED600">GRED 600</A>	Advanced Philosophical Foundations of Education<BR>
	<A HREF = "spedcourses.html#HLTH 550">HLTH 550</A>	Drug Studies	<P>

<B>Methods & Practicum:	30 credit hours</B><BR> 
	GRED 5xx*	Introductory Content Area Methods<BR>	
	<UL>	(one of the following courses:  <A HREF = "gredcourses500.html#GRED560">GRED 560</A>, <A HREF = "gredcourses500.html#GRED561">561</A>, <A HREF = "gredcourses500.html#GRED562">562</A>, <A HREF = "gredcourses500.html#GRED563">563</A>) </UL>
	GRED 5xx*	Observational Techniques & Exploratory Experiences
<UL>		(one of the following courses:  <A HREF = "gredcourses500.html#GRED570">GRED 570</A>, <A HREF = "gredcourses500.html#GRED571">571</A>,<A HREF = "gredcourses500.html#GRED572"> 572</A>, <A HREF = "gredcourses500.html#GRED573">573</A>)</UL>
	<A HREF = "gredcourses600.html#GRED603">GRED 603</A>	Seminar: Teaching in Secondary Schools<BR>	
	<A HREF = "gredcourses600.html#GRED605">GRED 605</A>	Reading and Study Skills in the Secondary Content Area<BR>
	GRED 6xx 	Advanced Secondary Education<BR>	
	<UL>			(one of the following courses:  <A HREF = "gredcourses600.html#GRED606">GRED 606</A>, <A HREF = "gredcourses600.html#GRED608">608</A>, <A HREF = "gredcourses600.html#GRED609">609</A>,<A HREF = "gredcourses600.html#GRED610"> 610</A> <BR> 
		   or	GRED 6xx  Sec. Content Area Methods Elective)</UL>
	<A HREF = "gredcourses650.html#GRED697">GRED 697</A>	Supervised Clinical Experience/Student Teaching (6 credit hours)<BR>
<A HREF = "gredcourses600.html#GRED613">	GRED 613</A>	Teaching Internship   (6 credit hours)<BR>
	<A HREF = "gredcourses650.html#GRED678">GRED 678</A>	Student Teaching Seminar: Issues and Ideas in American Education  (3 credit hours)<P>

<B>Electives:	6 credit hours</B><BR>
	Two 3-credit hour electives** (under advisement)<P>	

<B>Culminating Experience</B>:<BR>
	- Passing score on the ATS-W portions of the New York State Teacher Certification Exam<BR>
	- Successful completion of a Culminating Experience in the School of Education.<BR>
<UL>	NOTE:  The CST portion of the NYSTCE is required for permanent certification.</UL>

*must be taken concurrently<BR>
**<A HREF = "gredcourses650.html#GRED677">GRED 677</A> Development and Learning for Teachers is strongly recommended if undergraduate work does not include a course in developmental, adolescent or educational psychology.</FONT><P>
<IMG  Align=Top SRC="GREY_LINE.gif"><P>

