<DT><DT></BODY>
<DD>     <DD>     <!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=5><CENTER><B><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#FF659D">Lesson Plan  1-  Ecosystems</FONT></B></CENTER> </FONT><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR><CENTER><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#290A64"><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="lespone"><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="lesptwo">Task Analysis</A></A></FONT></CENTER><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <CENTER><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#290A64"><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="assmnt#assessment2">Summative Assessment</A></FONT></CENTER><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <CENTER><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="assmnt#port2">Portfolio Assessment</A></CENTER>
<DD>     <DD>     <!-- Horizontal Line Tag --><HR WIDTH=100% SIZE=3 NOSHADE>
<DD>     <DD>     <!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4><B><B><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#FF659D">Lesson Target</FONT> </B></B></FONT>  <BR>
<DD>     <DD>          Interactions <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4><B><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#FF659D">Science Concept:</FONT></B></FONT><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Ecosystems  Ecotones<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Species Identification and Classification<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4><B><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#FF659D">Science Skills:</FONT></B></FONT><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Gathering and Identifying<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Charting and Illustrating<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Observing and Listening<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4><B><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#FF659D">Interdisciplinary Connection:</FONT></B></FONT><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Ecology<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Duration :1 week<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4><B><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#FF659D">Lesson outcomes:</FONT></B></FONT><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <STRONG> </STRONG>
<DD>     <DD>     Students will:<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     1. Create their own quadrants <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     2. Gather and Identify Species using field guides<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     3. Complete DEC Identification cards<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     4. Recognize evidence of human interaction<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     5. Define Ecosystem<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     6. Relate that each organism has its own ecosystem<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     7. Discuss and explain the interacions between ecosystems and               ecotones 
<DD>     <DD>              
<DD>     <DD>     8. Draw descriptive maps of their quadrants <BR>  9.  Design an ecosystem collage<BR><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     
<DD>     <DD>     <!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4><B><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#FF659D">Overview:</FONT></B></FONT><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     In this lesson on ecosystems students will be examining the ecosystems present at 
<DD>     <DD>     the Oswegotchie River using the activity "The Edge of Home" from <EM>Project Aquatic</EM>
<DD>     <DD>       p. 68 
<DD>     <DD>     </BODY>
