<DD>     <DD>     <OL>
<DD>     <DD>     <LI>   Free write in their journals what significance the Oswegatchie <!-- List Tag --><DL>
<DD>     River has on their lives
</DL> 
<DD>     <DD>     <LI>  Interview a long time Gouverneur resident in regard to the <!-- List Tag --><DL>
<DD>     significance the O.R. has had on the town
</DL>
<DD>     <DD>     <LI>  Study maps to investigate possible reasons for town                     location<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <LI>  Identify economic benefits of the river (mills, mining, food,                <!-- List Tag --><DL>
<DD>     etc...)
</DL>
<DD>     <DD>     <LI>  Design a mind-map to inter-relate the impact of the O.R. on                     
<DD>     <DD>      their daily lives<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <LI>  Discuss the vital components neccessary for a successful                town<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <LI>  Create a town which contains all the elements for success *<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     * Using activity "Making My City" from  <EM>Outlook: The Earth</EM>
<DD>     <DD>       by            David V. McCalley p. 73<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     </OL>
<DD>     <DD>     <!-- Font Tag --><B><FONT SIZE=4><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#199161">Overview:</FONT></FONT></B><BR>
<DD>     <DD>      Lesson plan 1 will be an introduction to Project Oswegatchie River in which all students will participate. This lesson is designed to increase students awareness of the inter-relatedness of  the Oswegatchie River and their lives in the town of Gouverneur. 
