<DT><DT><TITLE>leseit</TITLE>
<DT><DT></HEAD>
<DT><DT><BODY BACKGROUND="back2.gif">
<DD>     <DD>     <B><!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=5><CENTER><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#00FF00">Lesson Plan #7- Animals</FONT></CENTER></FONT></B><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <CENTER><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#290A64"><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="lespeig">Task Analysis</A></A></FONT></CENTER><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <CENTER><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#290A64"><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="assmnt">Summative Assessment</A></FONT></CENTER><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <CENTER><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="assmnt#port8">Portfolio Assessment</A></CENTER>
<DD>     <DD>     <!-- Horizontal Line Tag --><HR WIDTH=100% SIZE=3 NOSHADE>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <B><!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#00FF00">Lesson Target:</FONT></FONT></B>   <BR>
<DD>     <DD>      Limiting Factors &amp; <BR>
<DD>     <DD>                     Evolutionary Adaptation  <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <B><!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#00FF00">Science Concept:</FONT></FONT></B></B><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Adaptation, classification, limiting factors<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <B><!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#00FF00">Science Skills:</FONT></FONT></B><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Listening and observing<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Charting and illustrating<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Analyze and predicting<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <B><!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#00FF00">Interdisciplinary Connection:</FONT></FONT></B><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Art used to illustrate the perfect animal for the ecosystem studied.<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Duration: 1 week<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <B><!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#00FF00">Lesson outcomes:</FONT></FONT></B><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     
<DD>     <DD>     <H3> </H3>
<DD>     <DD>     <B><!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4>Students will:</FONT></B><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <OL>
<DD>     <DD>     <LI>In a group activity explain and discuss how limiting factors are    <DD>illustrated by the water barrel technique. <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <LI>Explain what different factors are important for survival.<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <LI>Explain and discuss how organisms adapt to an environment due <DD>to the limiting factors discussed.<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <LI>Make models of tracks to be used to identify some animals living   <DD> in the observed ecosystem.<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <LI>Relate limiting factors, adaptation and organisms observed.<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <LI>Draw what would be the perfect animal for the environment.<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     </OL>
<DD>     <DD>     <B><!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#00FF00">Overview:</FONT></FONT></B><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     In this lesson the students will relate limiting factors and evolutionary adaptation to the ecosystem that they observe at the Oswegatchie River sites.<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     
<DD>     <DD>     </BODY>
<DD>     <DD>     </HTML>
