<DT><DT></BODY>
<DD>     <DD>     <B><!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=5><CENTER><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#290A64">Lesson Plan #2 - Energy Cycles</FONT></CENTER></FONT></B><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR><BR><CENTER><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#290A64"><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="lespthr">Task Analysis</A></A></A></FONT></CENTER><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <CENTER><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#290A64"><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="assmnt#assessment3">Summative Assessment</A></FONT></CENTER><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <CENTER><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="assmnt#port3">Portfolio Assessment</A></CENTER>
<DD>     <DD>     <!-- Horizontal Line Tag --><HR WIDTH=100% SIZE=3 NOSHADE>
<DD>     <DD>      <B><!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#290A64">Lesson Target:</FONT></FONT></B>   <BR>
<DD>     <DD>         Energy's role in the Ecosystem <BR>
<DD>     <DD>              various cycles involved in it      <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <B><!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#290A64">Science Concept:</FONT></FONT></B><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Limiting factors  Abiotic factors<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Water Cycle   Biotic factors<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Nutrient Cycles<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <B><!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#290A64">Science Skills:</FONT></FONT></B><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Analysis  inference<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     communication interpretation<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     discussion  visualization<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     generalization demonstration<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Interdisciplinary Connection:<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Art, Language Arts<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Duration: 1 week<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <B><!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#290A64">Lesson outcomes:</FONT></FONT></B><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     
<DD>     <DD>     <H3> </H3>
<DD>     <DD>     <B><!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4>Students will:</FONT></B><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <OL>
<DD>     <DD>     <LI>Study the main energy source- the sun.  Understand the      <!-- List Tag --><DL>
<DD>     significance of the sun and their inter-relatedness between    biotic and abiotic.
</DL>
<DD>     <DD>     <LI>Be able to draw the water cycle from learned material.<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <LI>Study the nutrient cycles and hypothesize the reasons for each    <!-- List Tag --><DL>
<DD>     interaction.
</DL>
<DD>     <DD>     <LI>Brainstorm to generate ideas which show knowledge of the     <!-- List Tag --><DL>
<DD>     nutrient cycles.
</DL><DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     </OL>
<DD>     <DD>     <B><!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#290A64">Overview:</FONT></FONT></B><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     In this section on energy in the Ecosystem and the nutrient cycles. These cycles are 
<DD>     <DD>     integral to the functioning of the Ecosystem.  The students will study these importances.
<DD>     <DD>     </BODY>
<DD>     <DD>     </HTML>
<DD>     </DL>
