<DT><DT><BODY BACKGROUND="back2.gif">
<DD>     <DD>     <!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=5 COLOR="#FFFEB5"><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#A27314"><CENTER>Lesson Plan #6 - Photosynthesis</CENTER></FONT></FONT><BR><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <CENTER><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#290A64"><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="lespsev">Task Analysis</A></A></FONT></CENTER><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <CENTER><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#290A64"><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="assmnt">Summative Assessment</A></FONT></CENTER><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <CENTER><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="assmnt#port7">Portfolio Assessment</A></CENTER>
<DD>     <DD>     <!-- Horizontal Line Tag --><HR WIDTH=100% SIZE=3 NOSHADE>
<DT><DD>     
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4 COLOR="#A27314">Lesson Target:</FONT>   <BR>
<DD>     <DD>       Photosynthesis      <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4 COLOR="#A27314">Science Concept:</FONT><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Respiration in animals and plants, Oxygen, Carbon Dioxide and sugar   in photosynthesis. 
<DD>     <DD>      Animal and plant relation due to photosynthesis.<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4 COLOR="#A27314">Science Skills:</FONT><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Observation analyzing and prediction<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Hypothesizing and reproduction<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4 COLOR="#A27314">Interdisciplinary Connection:</FONT><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Duration: 1 week<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4 COLOR="#A27314">Lesson outcomes:</FONT><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     
<DD>     <DD>     <H3> </H3>
<DD>     <DD>     Students will:<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <OL>
<DD>     <DD>     <LI>Discuss in a group the energy from the sun and how this is    <DD> converted in plant photosynthesis.<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <LI>Analyze results already observed and make predictions of how  <DD>  tests were performed to obtain these results.<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <LI>Use their knowledge of photosynthesis to explain observed <DD>results.<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <LI>Use the scientific method to analyze observations and find the    <DD>original hypothesis used.<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     </OL>
<DD>     <DD>     <!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4 COLOR="#A27314">Overview:</FONT><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     In this lesson the students will use group discussion to analyze the sun's use in the ecosystem with direction toward photosynthesis.  A Photosynthesis "Dry Lab" will be used to have the students work back from observations to construct a lab.  The original hypothesis used will be the final result and thus show knowledge of the scientific 
<DD>     <DD>     method.
<DD>     <DD>     </BODY>
<DD>     <DD>     </HTML>
<DD>     </DL>
</DL>
