<DD>     <DD>     <!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4 COLOR="#66081E">Lesson Target:</FONT>   <BR>
<DD>     <DD>       Recreation  & Employment <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4 COLOR="#66081E">Science Concept:</FONT><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Conservation <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Responsible Environmental Action<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4 COLOR="#66081E">Science Skills:</FONT><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Analysis   Application <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Classification  Mapping<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Problem Solving<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4 COLOR="#66081E">Interdisciplinary Connection:</FONT><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Economics, Social Sciences<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Duration: 1 week <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4 COLOR="#66081E">Lesson outcomes:</FONT><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     
<DD>     <DD>     <H3> </H3>
<DD>     <DD>     <!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4 COLOR="#66081E">Students will:</FONT><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <OL>
<DD>     <DD>     <LI>  Represent and defend a particular interest group (ie. Factory,           <DD>     residential, farmer, fisherman, etc...)  <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <LI>  Discuss and explain the effects of the interest group on the           <DD>    environment <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <LI>  Design and explain land use maps      <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <LI>  Identify positive and negative human actions in regards to the <DD> River<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <LI>  Discuss ways to improve land use in Gouverneur  <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     </OL>
<DD>     <DD>     <!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4 COLOR="#66081E">Overview:</FONT><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     In this lesson on human interaction with regard to recreation and employment, students will evaluate the positions held by different interest groups.  These positions will be assessed on their impact to the Oswegotchie River and positive alternatives will be discussed.<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Activity:  "Dragonfly Pond" from <EM>Project Aquatic</EM>
<DD>     <DD>      p. 154 <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     
