<DD>     <!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=5 COLOR="#FF0000"><CENTER>Lesson Plan #8 - Food Chains and Trophic Pyramids</CENTER></FONT><BR><BR>
<DD>     <CENTER><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#290A64"><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="lespnin">Task Analysis</A></A></FONT></CENTER><BR>
<DD>     <CENTER><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#290A64"><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="assmnt">Summative Assessment</A></FONT></CENTER><BR>
<DD>     <CENTER><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="assmnt#port9">Portfolio Assessment</A></CENTER>
<DD>     <!-- Horizontal Line Tag --><HR WIDTH=100% SIZE=3 NOSHADE>

</DL>
<BR>
<!-- List Tag --><DL>
<!-- List Tag --><DL>
<DD>     <DD>     <!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4 COLOR="#FF0000">Lesson Target:</FONT><BR>
<DD>     <DD>                    Relationships in an ecosystem<BR>
<DD>     <DD>             <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4 COLOR="#FF0000">Science Concept:</FONT><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Relationships in ecosystems, including food chains and trophic   pyramids.<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4 COLOR="#FF0000">Science Skills:</FONT><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Observation<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Communicating and discussing<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Organization<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Prediction and analyzation<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4 COLOR="#FF0000">Interdisciplinary Connection:</FONT><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Math data table and computation.<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Physical Education for human trophic pyramid.<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Art for food web assessment.<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Duration: 1 week<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4 COLOR="#FF0000">Lesson outcomes:</FONT><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     
<DD>     <DD>     <H3> </H3>
<DD>     <DD>     <!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4 COLOR="#FF0000">Students will:</FONT><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <OL>
<DD>     <DD>     <LI>Work individually to work as "prey" and compete.<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <LI>Work as a group to analyze effects of relationships.<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <LI>Explain how competition works in nature.<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <LI>Explain how food webs interact for their own specific ecosystem <DD>   in "My own little world."<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <LI>Explain how different food webs can be organized into a trophic  <DD>  pyramid for the specific ecosystem studied.<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <LI>Relate trophic pyramids to actual laws of nature.<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     <DD>     </OL>
<DD>     <DD>     <!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4 COLOR="#FF0000">Overview:</FONT><BR>
<DD>     <DD>     Students will evaluate a predator prey relationship and relate it to their own individual ecosystem.  The students will then relate this to trophic pyramids for observed ecosystem sites and explore actual laws of nature that govern pyramids.<BR>
<DD>     <DD>     <BR>
<DD>     </DL>
