<BODY>
<B><!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=5>Lesson Plan #12 - Weather Effects</FONT></B><BR><BR>
<CENTER><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#290A64"><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="lespttn">Task Analysis</A></A></FONT></CENTER><BR>
<CENTER><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#290A64"><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="assmnt">Assessment</A></FONT></CENTER><BR>
<!-- Horizontal Line Tag --><HR WIDTH=100% SIZE=3 NOSHADE>

<BR>
Lesson Target   <BR>
   Weather effects     <BR>
<BR>
Science Concept:<BR>
seasons, water erosion, precipitation, temperatures<BR>
<BR>
Science Skills:<BR>
Observations<BR>
Data Collecting<BR>
Analyze and Predicting<BR>
<BR>
Interdisciplinary Connection:<BR>
Earth Science, Geology, Physical Science.  By performing certain   experiments, including 
the data taking and chart tables, to analyze   and the effects on the terrestrial-aquatic 
community.<BR>
<BR>
Duration: 1 week<BR>
<BR>
Lesson outcomes:<BR>

<H3> </H3>
Students will:<BR>
<OL>
<LI>In a group activity, observe the physical changes and      scientific concepts which 
result from freezing.<BR>
(frozen water experiment- 474 book p.87)<BR>
<LI>Discover that heat causes water to turn to vapor, and cold     causes vapor to turn 
back to water.<BR>
(cleaning water:Heat,cold and Vapor Experiment- book     474 p.89)<BR>
<LI>Understand the different consistencies of soils; how the     weather affects this 
(soil samples Experiment- book 474    p. 358-60) <BR>
<LI>Analyze the affects of erosion on the river bed community<BR>
<LI>Learn how to maintain a daily journal with weather      observations.<BR>
<BR>
</OL>
Overview:<BR>
In this lesson on seasonal changes, students will recognize that weather affects every 
component of life; not only in the natural  environment, but how it applies to them 
personally.
</BODY>
</HTML>
