<HTML> 
<HEAD><TITLE>Social & Communication Skills</TITLE></HEAD> 
<BODY> 
Each unit plan should focus on developing a specified social and / or communication skill throughout all lessons of the unit.  Pupils should know what the specified skill is and should assess their own progress in practicing the skill.  A few skill are emphasized each year, and are practiced in several different units over the course of the year.  Examples of social skills and communication skills focused upon in grades 1 - 6 in the BSCS program are given below.</P><P>



<DD>     <DD>     <!-- List Tag --><DL>Grade Level:									         		Team Skill							/					Social Skill
<DT><DT>
<DT><DT><DT><!-- List Tag --><UL>
<DT><DT><DT><LI><LI><LI>		<!-- List Tag --><DL>
<DT><DT><DD>     <DT>	1:											Share the things you use		/			Shared leadership
<DT><DT><DD>     <DT><LI><LI><LI>			2:											Listen when others talk			/			Communication
<DT><DT><DD>     <DT><LI><LI><LI>			3:											          Take turns talking   /       										Shared leadership
<DT><DT><DD>     <DT><LI><LI><LI>			4:											Share your ideas						/					Communication
<DT><DT><DD>     <DT><LI><LI><LI>			5:											Talk about several answers before choosing one
<DT><DT><DD>     <DT><LI><LI><LI>			6:								Ask questions to help you understand one another's point of view
<DT><DT><DT><DT></UL>
<DT><DT><DT></DL>
<DT><DT></DL>
</DL>
</DL>
</DOC>
